column1: Data collected as part of Edwin Viramontes's Semester by the Bay internship project. Expanding work done by Brian Ulaski on beach wrack.

column3: unique value assigned to each transect location
meter mark along 50 m transect line
total percent of 0.5 x 0.5 quadrat filled with wrack
percent of 0.5 x 0.5 quadrat filled with seagrass wrack
percent of 0.5 x 0.5 quadrat filled with algal wrack

abbreviations for macroalgae separated by | 
AGCL = Agarum clathratum
FUGA = Fucus gardineri
NELU  = Nereocystis luetkeana
ULVA = Ulva spp.
DESP = Desmarestia spp.
ALMA = Alaria marginata
Brown = Unidentified brown alga
Red = Unidentified red alga
Green = Unidentified green alga
percent of 0.5 x 0.5 quadrat filled with terrestrial wrack
percent of 0.5 x 0.5 quadrat filled with human debris
deepest depth of wrack in cm
width centered on transect point of wrackline in cm
